column10: A driver heading westbound on Duke St. ran the red light at Duke and Arell Ct.  A pedestrian was starting to cross Duke St. (from the northwest corner of the intersection).  I was approaching the intersection (heading south on Arell Ct), when I saw the car about to run the red light, as well as the pedestrian starting to cross.  I honked my horn to alert the pedestrian about the impending danger.  This is captured on my dashcam video here:  https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-M-xTOpu7GfBG6KfH6wQXLfpugq1K21B/view?usp=share_link
column21: I reported this incident (and shared the dashcam video) via Alexandria's Alex311 system.  I've been requesting that the city install red light cameras at this intersection due to the frequency of cars running the red light and causing accidents.
